text:
(1)
147-151 East 23rd Street, north side, between Lexington and Third Avenue, seen across excavation for the erection of the new building of the College of the City of New York. At the left is Kenmore Hall; at the right is the Hospital Supply Company.
March 12, 1928.
P.L. Sperr.

(2)
Kenmore Hall, 143-147 East 23rd Street, and adjoining buildings, seen across the City College excavation.
March 12, 1928.
P.L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: 23rd Street - Lexington
